                    <!-- Detailed Instruction Notes -->
                    <h2 class="section-header text-xl">Detailed Instruction Notes</h2>
                    
                    <!-- Introduction -->
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Introduction (12 minutes)</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                            <li>Begin with an icebreaker question: "Who has had a job or knows someone who has? What was it like?"</li>
                            <li>Present the key definitions and differences between jobs and careers using relatable examples</li>
                            <li>Facilitate a brief whole-class discussion on why this distinction matters for students now</li>
                            <li>Connect to students' current experiences with part-time jobs or extracurricular activities</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Key Concepts -->
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Key Concepts (15 minutes)</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                            <li>Introduce the concept of human capital using accessible language</li>
                            <li>Break students into small groups to discuss how different jobs build different skills</li>
                            <li>Reconvene for a guided discussion on financial implications</li>
                            <li>Create a comparison chart of job vs. career financial outcomes on the whiteboard</li>
                            <li>Address common misconceptions about jobs always being "less than" careers</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Real-World Examples -->
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Real-World Examples (10 minutes)</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                            <li>Present Alex and Taylor scenarios (one job-focused, one career-focused)</li>
                            <li>Pose discussion questions about their different approaches to similar positions</li>
                            <li>Have students predict future outcomes for both individuals</li>
                            <li>Emphasize that both paths have valid reasons based on individual circumstances</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Skill Builder Activity -->
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Skill Builder Activity (10 minutes)</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                            <li>Explain the Career Path Mapping activity structure and objectives</li>
                            <li>Guide students through completing their individual career roadmaps</li>
                            <li>Emphasize this is a first draft that will be refined over time</li>
                            <li>Encourage realistic but ambitious selections in each category</li>
                            <li>Ensure students save their work for Day 2</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Reflection & Wrap-up -->
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Reflection & Wrap-up (8 minutes)</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                            <li>Allow individual reflection time for students to consider their own path</li>
                            <li>Invite volunteers to share insights from their reflections</li>
                            <li>Summarize key takeaways about the job/career distinction</li>
                            <li>Preview Day 2 Learning Lab activities</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Discussion Prompts -->
                    <h2 class="section-header text-xl">Discussion Prompts</h2>
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <div class="mb-4">
                            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">For Introduction:</h3>
                            <p>"Why might someone choose a job over a career, or vice versa?"</p>
                            <p class="mt-2"><strong>Expected responses:</strong> immediate income needs, flexibility, passion for a field, long-term growth</p>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div class="mb-4">
                            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">For Deeper Exploration:</h3>
                            <p>"What skills from a fast-food job might transfer to a corporate setting?"</p>
                            <p class="mt-2"><strong>Expected responses:</strong> customer service, time management, teamwork, handling pressure</p>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div class="mb-4">
                            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">For Real-World Examples:</h3>
                            <p>"What specific actions could Alex take to become more career-focused?"</p>
                            <p class="mt-2"><strong>Expected responses:</strong> seeking additional responsibilities, asking for training opportunities, networking within the company</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Differentiation Strategies -->
                    <h2 class="section-header text-xl">Differentiation Strategies</h2>
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">For advanced students:</h3>
                        <p>Encourage research on salary progressions in their field of interest; suggest creating a basic financial projection based on career research</p>
                        
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2 mt-4">For struggling students:</h3>
                        <p>Provide structured templates with examples for the Career Path Mapping activity; offer one-on-one guidance during independent work</p>
                        
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2 mt-4">For ELL students:</h3>
                        <p>Use visual comparisons between jobs and careers; provide key vocabulary list with definitions in advance</p>
                    </div>
                    
