                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Key Day 1 Concepts to Review:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>Distinction between jobs and careers</li>
                            <li>Human capital and its importance</li>
                            <li>Career planning as a long-term process</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Podcast Discussion Points:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>How jobs can be stepping stones in a career journey</li>
                            <li>Financial impacts of career-oriented thinking</li>
                            <li>Connection between education, skills, and career progression</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Learning Lab Introduction:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                            <li>Frame today's activities as building on Day 1 foundations</li>
                            <li>Emphasize practical application of career planning concepts</li>
                            <li>Explain that the end product will be a usable career implementation portfolio</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Activity 1 -->
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Activity 1: Career Pathway Research (15 minutes)</h3>
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Setup Instructions:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>Students should have access to career research tools</li>
                            <li>Allow individual work with occasional peer discussion</li>
                            <li>Provide research guidance handouts if needed</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Facilitation Steps:</h4>
                        <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>Guide students to appropriate research resources for their specific career interests (2 minutes)</li>
                            <li>Model how to evaluate the credibility of career information (3 minutes)</li>
                            <li>Allow independent research time (8 minutes)</li>
                            <li>Brief share-out of key findings (2 minutes)</li>
                        </ol>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Key Teaching Points:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>Focus on researching education requirements, typical career progression, and salary ranges</li>
                            <li>Look for trends and growth potential in chosen fields</li>
                            <li>Consider multiple paths to the same career goal</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Monitoring Guidance:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                            <li>Check that students are using reliable sources</li>
                            <li>Look for depth rather than breadth in research</li>
                            <li>Help students who are struggling to find specific information</li>
                            <li>Encourage note-taking in a structured format</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Activity 2 -->
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Activity 2: Obstacle Analysis (12 minutes)</h3>
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Setup Instructions:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>Provide obstacle analysis template</li>
                            <li>Arrange for small group discussion</li>
                            <li>Display examples of common obstacles</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Facilitation Steps:</h4>
                        <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>Introduce the concept of anticipating obstacles as part of strategic planning (2 minutes)</li>
                            <li>Share examples of common obstacles and potential strategies (3 minutes)</li>
                            <li>Facilitate small group discussions for obstacle identification (3 minutes)</li>
                            <li>Guide individual work on mitigation strategies (4 minutes)</li>
                        </ol>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Key Teaching Points:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>Obstacles can be financial, educational, personal, or systemic</li>
                            <li>Strategy development should be specific and actionable</li>
                            <li>Different obstacles require different approaches</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Monitoring Guidance:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                            <li>Ensure strategies are realistic and specific</li>
                            <li>Encourage peer feedback on strategy effectiveness</li>
                            <li>Look for students who may need help identifying realistic solutions</li>
                            <li>Push advanced students to consider multiple contingency plans</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Activity 3 -->
                    <div class="mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Activity 3: Human Capital Investment (10 minutes)</h3>
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Setup Instructions:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>Provide human capital investment planning templates</li>
                            <li>Arrange for individual work with teacher circulation</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Facilitation Steps:</h4>
                        <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>Review the concept of human capital from Day 1 (2 minutes)</li>
                            <li>Guide students in identifying specific skills needed for their career path (3 minutes)</li>
                            <li>Support students in creating targeted investment plans (5 minutes)</li>
                        </ol>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Key Teaching Points:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-2">
                            <li>Emphasize both formal education and skill development</li>
                            <li>Connect investments to specific career outcomes</li>
                            <li>Consider cost-benefit analysis for different investments</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 mb-1">Monitoring Guidance:</h4>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                            <li>Check for alignment between career goals and investment plans</li>
                            <li>Look for specificity in skill development strategies</li>
                            <li>Help students prioritize investments based on impact</li>
                            <li>Encourage thinking about both technical and soft skills</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <!-- Reflection & Wrap-up -->
